               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183701020088"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370102-name-608" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-608" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-608" type="surname" value="COPSEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-608" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD COPSEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Norton, in Essex, and am a butcher. I loft a coat off my horse, on the 3rd of January, about a quarter put six o'clock in the morning, while I was gone to Mr. Venables—I was away about two minutes, and it was gone when I returned—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370102-name-609" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-609" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-609" type="surname" value="BARKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-609" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BARKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a patrol of Farringdon-ward. I was on duty, and saw the prisoner take the coat off the horse's back in Newgate-street—he put it on his arm, and ran down Butcherhall-lane—I took him there with it—he said he had found it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. There was another young man with me. I had received some money the night before, and we staid out all night—when this officer came to me he said, "I thought it was another that took it, but 1 could not get him." <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. No, I said I did not think it would be you that took the coat; I thought it would have been your companion: because I had seen him take the trouble of taking up some hay, and giving it to the horse.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370102-name-610" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-610" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-610" type="surname" value="HIGHLAND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-610" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS HIGHLAND</persName>
                  </hi>. I was with the officer, and saw the coat found on the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
